		<td><b>FDS on PowerPak</b></td>
	</tr>
	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />Behold, I give you:
<br />
<br /><a href="http://home.comcast.net/~olimar/NES/powerpak_fds.zip" class="postlink">FDS on PowerPak</a>
<br />
<br />Consider it a proof of concept at this point. Few games work, I'm still trying to figure out why. I just wanted to show that it's doable.  It uses an unmodified bios; the low level disk stuff is emulated, I didn't need to write new loading routines.  I'll need to do it eventually though, to handle disk switching.

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


