	<tr>
		<td colspan="2"><hr class="sep" />This is a very cool hack.  I didn't see why it couldn't be possible -- the PowerPak mapper is configurable enough to give you the RAM and the timer IRQs of the FDS.
<br />
<br />On my Famicom+PowerPak setup, several of the games (Super Mario Bros., etc.) have glitchy CHR graphics, or just general PPU screw-ups.  SMB2's jumping is all screwy too.  I'm not asking you to fix that, but I wonder what could be causing such strange bugs...
<br />
<br />At least many FDS games' intro scenes can be run on the PowerPak now.   <img src="./images/smilies/icon_smile.gif" alt=":)" title="Smile" />

		

		</td>
	</tr>
	</table>


